Documentation
Project documentation is generated using Doxygen and rendered as a browsable HTML site.
The documentation includes:
  Class descriptions
  Public and private members
  Inheritance diagrams
  Dependency graphs (via Graphviz)

Prerequisites
Before generating documentation, install:
  Doxygen
  Graphviz (required for UML and class diagrams)
macOS (Homebrew)
  brew install doxygen
  brew install graphviz
Ubuntu / Debian
  sudo apt install doxygen graphviz
Windows
  Download installers from:
  https://www.doxygen.nl/download.html
  https://graphviz.org/download/

Generating Documentation
From the root of the project directory, run:
doxygen Doxyfile
This will generate a new folder:
html/

Viewing Documentation
Open the generated documentation in your browser:
open html/index.html      # macOS
or
xdg-open html/index.html  # Linux
You can also manually open html/index.html in any web browser.

Viewing Diagrams
If Graphviz is installed correctly, the documentation will include:
  Class diagrams
  Inheritance hierarchies
  Collaboration graphs
